(5687, 11, 'Pig production processed and marketed on-farm Economic characteristics', 'A system has been developed that profiles farms according to their economic profitability.\r\nThe system has identified three groups on the basis of the percentages of pigs processed on-farm.\r\nProducing, processing and selling local farm-produced products generates an economic activity that adds value to the quality\r\nof the product and the expertise of the farmer, offering higher sale prices that are also independent of market fluctuations.\r\nHowever, the production process has to be fully controlled in order to guarantee constant food quality, attract customers and\r\nsecure that first purchase, as a prerequisite to generating repeat business and running this diversification system.\r\nThe mean EBITDA of this sample population, not counting family benefits, is 2.43 â‚¬/kg carcass.', 'Delisle C;Frotin P;', 'Vol.31 6', 1228086000, '', '1112', 'caractÃ©ristiques;commercialisation;Ã©conomie;Ã©levage;porc;porcs;', '11', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(5688, 11, 'The 12th ESDAR Congress (European Society of Domestic Animal Reproduction)', 'A selection of the highlight ''pork-related'' communications have been reviewed. Certain communications targeted more towards\r\nother species nevertheless open up perspectives for research in pigs. Indeed, a total of 173 posters (30-odd related to pig\r\nfarming) presented the most recent progress made in research. Around 15 firms were there to unveil the latest technological\r\nbreakthroughs available to CIA (livestock breeding centres) and veterinary surgeons. The AI-Vets forum addressed issues  specifically related to insemination, particularly in pig breeding.\r\nThe 2009 edition of the ESDAR congress will be held at Ghent in Belgium, over the 10th to12th September.\r\nThe IFIP is scheduled to lead a workshop dedicated to hyperprolific sows.\r\nhttp://www.esdar.org/', 'Boulot S;', 'Vol.31 6', 1228086000, '', '1113', 'animal domestique;Belgique;CIA;congrÃ¨s;ESDAR;reproduction;sÃ©lection;travail;truie;truie hyperprolifique;', '11', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
