(5679, 11, 'Localized sanitation processes : benefits of the ''steam vacuum'' treatment in the management of fecal soiling on carcasses', 'This study was designed to assess the efficiency of the steam vacuum process as an alternative to knife trimming for processing\r\ncarcasses that present visible signs of fecal soiling at the critical slaughter step. The results show that both methods are able to reduce fecal contamination on soiled carcasses down to control values. However, for a comparable effect (> 2 Log), the steam\r\nvacuum preserved more marketable carcass.\r\nIndustrial-scale slaughterhouses can use the steam vacuum as an alternative to traditional knife trimming on carcasses presenting visible signs of fecal soiling.', 'Le Roux A;Minvielle B;Lhommeau T;', 'Vol.31 6', 1228086000, '', '1104', 'carcasse;dÃ©contamination;souillure fÃ©cale;steam vacuum;traitement assainissant;porc', '11', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
