(5647, 11, 'Regulations governing the importation and use of GMO in the EU : How might this impact on the supply of raw materials to livestock feed sectors ?', 'This study reviews the regulatory requirements governing the import, marketing and labelling of GMO in the EU and its member\r\nStates. It presents the opinions of importers and livestock feed industrials on the practical application of these requirements.\r\nIt assesses asynchronous authorisations and difficulties in securing supplies, which are set to become major concerns as of late\r\n2008. It also considers the possible future for non-GMO labelled sectors against a background of high-priced raw materials, and\r\nthe attitude of countries and sectors engaged in export.', 'Girard P;', 'Vol.31 4', 1217541600, '', '1072', 'rÃ©glementation;consÃ©quences;matiÃ¨res premiÃ¨res;Ã©tude;contraintes rÃ©glementaires;commercialisation;bilan;autorisation;filiÃ¨re;prix;exportateurs;graisses animales;alimentation;aliments;aliment;porc;', '11', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(5646, 11, 'An X-ray scanner to bolster the sector', 'The French pork sector recently acquired a mobile X-ray scanner through an investment provided by the Livestock Producers Board, Inaporc and the IFIP. This type of equipment, originally designed for use in medical diagnostics, is particularly well suited to measuring livestock body composition. It can be used to build 3D images based on differences in tissue density and to measure the proportions via image analysis. This type of equipment, already in use in several other countries, will enable the French pork sector to participate in designing a future European benchmark method for X-ray measurement of muscle content. Furthermore, as with applications already developed for both pigs and other species, sheep in particular, the X-ray scanner will be used for a range of R&D applications in the areas of product quality, genetics, foodstuffs or livestock management strategy.', 'Daumas G;Monziols M;', 'Vol.31 4', 1217541600, '', '1071', 'activitÃ©;alimentation;analyse;composition;composition corporelle;conduite;conduite d''Ã©levage;densitÃ©;dÃ©veloppement;diagnostic;filiÃ¨re;gÃ©nÃ©tique;mesure;mÃ©thode;muscle;porc;produit;produits;qualitÃ©;qualitÃ© des produits;rayons;rayons X;scanner;service;teneur;', '11', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
