(5564, 11, 'Slapmark-tattooing pigs with an air gun at weaning ; importance of compliance with the guidelines.', 'Authorisation was issued in late 2007 for four air gun models to be used to tattoo the ID code marking behind the shoulder on piglets. This article sets out the characteristics of each model. These air guns can only be used on grower-finisher\r\nfarms that fatten all their porkers on the same site.\r\nThis hardware proves more expensive than purchasing a straightforward slapmarker, but the initial investment can quickly pay off, especially given the time savings made.\r\nNevertheless, in order to guarantee that the tattoos are 100% readable when the pig arrives at the slaughterhouse, it is essential to follow the manufacturerâ€™s guidelines given in the instructions for use accompanying the authorised hardware.', 'Aubry A;', 'Vol.31 1', 1201820400, '', '989', 'pistolet pneumatique;porcs charcutiers;prÃ©conisation;respect;sevrage;tatouage;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
