(5500, 11, 'Cereals market : summer 2006, summer 2007 : still rising.', 'The rise in cereal prices has been practically continuous for the last year and more.\r\nIn 2006 the fall in European and world harvests put sharp pressure on prices. During the 2006-2007 campaign intervention\r\nstocks were released onto the European market. Imports of manioc and cereals increased.\r\nThe 2007-2008 campaign has started on an unfavourable note: European wheat and maize harvest down, European stocks much reduced, sharp rise in international wheat prices. Competition between food and biofuel crops, increasing vulnerability to unplanned events : The cereals markets have entered a new era.', 'Marouby H;', 'Vol.30 5', 1191189600, '', '925', 'cÃ©rÃ©ales;hausse;marchÃ©;', '11', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
