(5488, 11, 'Economical situation of French pig farming ; 2006 results', 'In 2006, pig farmers enjoyed an average 5% hike in pork revenue compared to 2005, while general food prices remained relatively static, up 1.7%. Food cost mark-ups and turnover showed clear improvement, up around 20% in 12 months with slight differences between industry sectors, a figure in excess of the trends observed in previous years. The mark-up improvement was bolstered by better overall technical results. Production costs on grower-finisher farms remained stable, at 1.24 â‚¬/kg carcass. Despite the overall technical gains made across the branch as a whole, there are still significant between-farm differences. These good 2006 results will have to underpin 2007, when market conditions are expected to slip. The profits made in 2006 should offer a ploughback opportunity to boost on-farm investment, which has been lacking in recent years.', 'Gourmelen C;Marouby H;', 'Vol.30 3', 1180648800, '', '913', 'France;rÃ©sultats;Ã©conomie;Ã©levage;', '11', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
