(5461, 11, 'Omega-3 fatty acids : their role in nutrition and health and its implication for pig breeding', 'A literature review of published work shows that an adapted feeding strategy (omega-3 enrichment mainly through the use of flax seed supplementation) is now a recognised means of modifying the proportion of\r\nomega-3 fatty acids in the lipid fraction of pork. This omega-3-enriched meat could help to balance the omega-6/omega-3 ratio in the human diet, if the amounts of lipids supplied were significant, in pursuance of dietary recommendations.', 'Vautier A;', 'Vol.30 1', 1170284400, '', '885', 'omÃ©ga 3;qualitÃ©;santÃ©;viande;viande de porc;', '11', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(5463, 11, 'Trends in pork quality over the last ten years', 'In the last ten years a strong mobilisation of breeders, producer groups, feed manufacturers, genetics experts and slaughterers has led to the production of leaner meat. Meat quality is constantly improving along with better control over pre-slaughter and slaughter conditions. Besides the technological quality, the health quality of meat is better controlled between breeding and slaughter-butchery (good hygiene practice guidelines and HACCP).\r\nOne of the next food safety challenges facing the industry will be the implementation of a â€˜hygiene packageâ€™ through guidelines for good breeding hygiene practice, and the qualification of piggeries for salmonella status by 2009. The pork industry must continue its efforts to improve meat quality while at the same time rising to new challenges: reassuring consumers, and offering easy-to-prepare and quick-cook products in response to societal demand.', 'Chevillon P;', 'Vol.30 1', 1170284400, '', '887', 'evolution;qualitÃ©;qualitÃ© hygiÃ©nique des viandes;qualitÃ© technologique;viande;viande de porc;', '11', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
