(5218, 11, 'CORPEN references for N, P, K, Cu and Zn in swine effluent', 'In 2003 CORPEN proposed new references for nitrogen, phosphorus and potassium, and later for copper and zinc.\r\nThese references take into account current pig farming performance, recent feeding systems that save nitrogen and phosphorus (standard and â€˜two-phaseâ€™ feeding), and also animal housing and the type of farm fertiliser produced (manure, litter).', 'Texier C;', 'Vol.27 3', 0, '2004  mai-juin', '642', 'Corpen;environnement;rejets;rÃ©fÃ©rences;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
