(5110, 11, 'Performance and longevity of sows according to ambient conditions and feeding during lactation', 'The study presented confirms earlier work showing that the lactation performance of sows was strongly depressed when the ambient temperature permanently exceeded 25Â°C. In addition we show that the sensitivity to heat varies among sows and affects their longevity in the herd. Also, although heavier weaned piglets were obtained by increasing the nutrient concentrations in the feed, the formula used did not mitigate the degraded condition of the sows. Other formulation patterns remain to be tested.', 'Quiniou N;', 'Vol.26 2', 0, '2003  mars-avril', '534', 'alimentation;ambiance;longÃ©vitÃ©;maternitÃ©;performances;truie;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(5109, 11, 'Piggeries : renovate or rebuild ?', 'One third of the total floor area of all farms is more than 20 years old and has been renovated twice or even three times, causing major problems. However, we can consider that the general state of French pig farming buildings is currently satisfactory.', 'Rousseau P;', 'Vol.26 2', 0, '2003  mars-avril', '533', 'bÃ¢timent;construire;porcheries;rÃ©nover;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(5108, 11, 'Low-cost pork production : in what conditions ? Situation in France, international comparisons, perspectives', 'This study shows that the lowest farm production costs in 2000 were 1.09 EUR/kg carcass. Five profiles were identified. Profile 1: moderate costs at all stages through good technical performance. Profile 2: very low prices of weaning sale feed, often produced on the farm. Profile 3: lowest labour costs owing to good productivity and to farming out. Profile 4: lowest depreciation and financial costs owing to old plant and buildings. Profile 5: Best technical results. The USA and Spain are still highly competitive because of less costly production factors and lighter societal constraints, despite poorer technical results. The EU accession of central European countries is not yet a source of serious competition owing to strong inertia.\r\nTechnical advancement, lowered prices of production factors and optimisation of farming systems are avenues to be explored.', 'Gourmelen C;', 'Vol.26 2', 0, '2003  mars-avril', '532', 'coÃ»t;coÃ»t de production;coÃ»ts;France;monde;perspectives;production;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
