(5059, 11, 'Optimising disinfecting', 'In this test the two methods for applying disinfectant (spraying and foam projection) gave equivalent decontamination results. However, in terms of work time and difficulty, foam was found preferable. A second disinfecting significantly improved the decontamination of the premises. Also, heat spraying reached areas with poor accessibility and proved less costly than foam.', 'CorrÃ©gÃ© I;Cornou C;', 'Vol.25 6', 0, '2002  novembre-dÃ©cembre', '481', 'dÃ©sinfection;sanitaire;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(5060, 11, 'Drying of walls and ventilation spaces', 'Heating was found to play a part in the optimisation of decontamination efficacy, especially in winter, when it helped surfaces dry quickly. Rapid drying of premises for at least 48 hours is preferable to providing ventilation spaces.', 'CorrÃ©gÃ© I;Cornou C;Rousseau P;', 'Vol.25 6', 0, '2002  novembre-dÃ©cembre', '482', 'chauffage;dÃ©sinfection;sanitaire;sÃ©chage;vide sanitaire;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(5061, 11, 'The process of emptying, cleaning and disinfection of slurry pits', 'The whole testing allowed it to prove the interest of emptying and washing the slurry pits (average cost of 4 â‚¬ per sow per year) at the level of bacteriological results. For an additional cost of 3 â‚¬, the disinfection\r\nof slurry pits only allows to reduce residual contamination of the concerned sites. It is therefore more judicious to replace it by a thermonebulization process.', 'CorrÃ©gÃ© I;Cornou C;', 'Vol.25 6', 0, '2002  novembre-dÃ©cembre', '483', 'dÃ©sinfection;nettoyage-dÃ©sinfection;prÃ©fosse;sanitaire;vidange;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(5062, 11, 'Comparison of three types of ventilation during 10 hours transport. Ambience and welfare of pigs', 'The aim of the study was to compare the simultaneous operation of three ventilation systems on three decks during a 10-hour journey, and to study the effects on the welfare of pigs of natural ventilation by\r\nflaps regulated by temperature sensors, blowers regulated by temperature sensors, and natural ventilation through opened flaps. The results depended strongly on the outside ambient conditions (notably temperature and air speed) and whether the truck was moving or stationary. This study was conducted with the ITP-COOPAGRI Brittany experimental truck financed by DGAL.', 'Chevillon P;Frotin P;Rousseau P;Prunier A;Le Roux A;Minvielle B;Boulard J;BouyssiÃ¨re M;Bataille G;', 'Vol.25 6', 0, '2002  novembre-dÃ©cembre', '485', 'ambiance;bien Ãªtre;camions de transport;transport;ventilation;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(5058, 11, 'Compared technical and economic performance of litter and full slatted flooring in fattening pens', 'Raising pigs on straw litter means extra costs at all production stages; in order of importance: labour, cost of straw, cost of feed and of piglets. Calculations based on certain assumptions give a production cost of\r\nover 0.13 â‚¬/kg carcass for pigs on litter. This extra cost can be recouped only through specific marketing circuits.', 'Laligant D;Rimoux D;Dutertre C;', 'Vol.25 6', 0, '2002  novembre-dÃ©cembre', '480', 'caillebotis;engraissement;GTE;litiÃ¨re;logement;performances;Ã©conomie;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
