(4755, 11, 'Cost-effectiveness of automated dipping,desirability of applying detergent solutions and estimating the cost of cleaning-disinfecting of livestock facilities', 'Cost-effectiveness of automated dipping : \r\nThe purpose of the trial described here was to compare automatic and manual dipping. Automatic dipping does not improve bacteriological results. It reduces the overall cost of the cleaning-disinfecting operations by 4%.\r\nDesirability of applying detergent solutions :\r\nThe application of a detergent solution optimises cleaning-disinfecting operations. At the present time only one in two livestock farms use detergents.\r\nEstimating the cost of cleaning-disinfecting of livestock facilities : \r\nThe importance of cleaning and disinfecting livestock facilities in health risk control is universally acknowledged.\r\nHere the different components are quantified for a â€œtypicalâ€ livestock farm in order to estimate the cost of the overall operation. Working time and quantities of products used are the main components of the cost of cleaning-disinfecting operations. These two components are particularly important because they constitute two determining factors for the successful decontamination of facilities.', 'CorrÃ©gÃ© I;Cornou C;SalaÃ¼n Y;', 'Vol.25 5', 0, '2002', '173', 'bÃ¢timent;coÃ»t;dÃ©tergent;nettoyage-dÃ©sinfection;sanitaire;trempage;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(4748, 11, '', '', 'Daumas G;', 'Vol.25 4', 0, '2002', '166', 'bilan annuel;carcasses;pesÃ©e-classement;qualitÃ© technologique;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(4749, 11, 'Treatment plants for pig farm effluent. Estimated costs and economic implications', 'Through the joint efforts of companies and farmers implementing different processes for treating pig farm effluent, it has been possible to collect technical and economic information to assess efficacy and calculate\r\ncosts for each process. The results obtained range widely, with costs remaining high. These results are linked to the type of process used and are sensitive to how the plant is run. The economic results presented state the costs specific to the treatment. Production costs and overall profitability range according to what proportion of the total liquid manure produced is treated. The pig farmer has to optimise not only the economic impact, but also the tax and social implications of the treatment by integrating treatment costs into overall business strategy.', 'TeffÃ¨ne O;', 'Vol.25 4', 0, '2002', '167', 'coÃ»t;environnement;lisier;stations de traitement;traitements;Ã©conomie;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(4750, 11, 'Cleaning-disinfecting of pig-farming premises and its governing factors', 'Control of cleaning and disinfecting operations thus requires a sound and methodical approach. No single step can be overlooked because each step influences the following one. The motivation of the personnel carrying out the operations, allowance for the specific characteristics of each farm and knowledge of good practice (e.g., calculation of and compliance with the quantities of agents required per shed) are among the prerequisites for successful cleaning-disinfecting.', 'CorrÃ©gÃ© I;Cornou C;', 'Vol.25 4', 0, '2002', '168', 'bÃ¢timent;nettoyage-dÃ©sinfection;sanitaire;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(4753, 11, 'Actinobacillus serology to monitor livestock health status', 'Health status monitoring of breeding and reproductive livestock requires being able to detect asymptomatic carriers of App. For this purpose, serology usefully complements the other available diagnostic approaches.', 'CorrÃ©gÃ© I;Kobisch M;Mieli L;', 'Vol.25 4', 0, '2002', '171', 'Actinobacillus;ELISA;sanitaire;sÃ©rologie;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
(4752, 11, 'Influence of floor and litter type on welfare during transport', 'This study shows that 1 cm of dry sawdust, i.e., 5 l per pig is enough to keep pigs in good condition during transport lasting 16 h. The sawdust provides greater comfort in winter owing to its insulating properties. It\r\nalso calms the pigs. In contrast, in hot weather, to prevent breathing problems and still keep the pigs clean it proves useful to dampen the sawdust by spraying the animals. Plastic-coated wire slatting is an alternative to litter. Its main disadvantage is cleaning and disinfecting the floor. The design of floor slatting and truck bodywork\r\nmust allow easy and quick washing of flooring. Lastly, as rubberized flooring is non-slip, the animals can move about more during the transport, which is useful for feeding and watering the animals.', 'Chevillon P;Frotin P;Rousseau P;', 'Vol.25 4', 0, '2002', '170', 'bien Ãªtre;litiÃ¨re;transport;type de sol;', '', '', '', 'n', '', 'o'),
